<TITLE> Iqbal Hasan Mahmud shifted to Dhaka for treatment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 4 (bdnews24.com) - Former BNP state minister Iqbal Hasan Mahmud was brought to Dhaka from Kashimpur jail for treatment, a jail official said Wednesday. He is now in Dhaka Central Jail where his wife, son and daughter have also been staying since Tuesday, deputy inspector general of prisons Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com. Mahmud was brought in at 5.30pm for dental treatment. Siddiqui said Mahmud would be sent back to Kashimpur jail after treatment, and it may take three days. Joint forces arrested the junior minister on Feb 4 on charges of corruption. Police arrested his wife Romana Mahmud and daughter Sara Hasin Mahmud Tuesday while his son Hasan Mahmud surrendered to the trial court the same day. The court later ordered them to jail. bdnews
